netraCtRscMIB.name: netraCtRscMIB

revisions.description: First version of MIB module SUN-SNMP-NETRA-CT-RSC-MIB.

netraCtRscMIB.description: The MIB module for the Netra ct 400/800 Remote System Control Products

netraCtRscAdminRscReset.name: netraCtRscAdminRscReset
netraCtRscAdminRscReset.description: Setting this will soft Reset only the RSC (Remote System Controller) card. The clear(2) setting is read-only for this variable. This variable will always read as clear(2).

netraCtRscAdminHostReset.name: netraCtRscAdminHostReset
netraCtRscAdminHostReset.description: Setting netraCtRscAdminHostReset will cause either send a break to the host, or will toggle a hard reset line. A break will be sent if netraCtRscPanicDump conatins the value of on(1).Otherwise, a hard reset will occur. The clear(2) setting is read-only for this variable. This variable will always reads as clear(2).

netraCtRscAdminXir.name: netraCtRscAdminXir
netraCtRscAdminXir.description: Sends a hardware xir pulse to the host when set to true. This variable resets itself to clear(2) after the negation of the pulse.

netraCtRscAdminNmi.name: netraCtRscAdminNmi
netraCtRscAdminNmi.description: Sends a hardware nmi pulse to the host when set to true. This variable resets itself to clear(2) after the negation of the pulse.

netraCtRscAdminBreak.name: netraCtRscAdminBreak
netraCtRscAdminBreak.description: Sends a break to the Host when this is set. The clear(2) setting is read-only for this variable. This variable will always read as clear(2).

netraCtRscGlobalPageFlag.name: netraCtRscGlobalPageFlag
netraCtRscGlobalPageFlag.description: An on(1) to this variable will enable paging for RSC alerts. An off(2) will disable paging.

netraCtRscGlobalEmailFlag.name: netraCtRscGlobalEmailFlag
netraCtRscGlobalEmailFlag.description: An on(1) to this variable will enable email for RSC alerts. An off(2) will disable email.

netraCtRscGlobalPPPFlag.name: netraCtRscGlobalPPPFlag
netraCtRscGlobalPPPFlag.description: serial configuration flag indicating whether PPP should be the default.

netraCtRscHostname.name: netraCtRscHostname
netraCtRscHostname.description: name of Host connected to RSC

netraCtRscCustomerInfo.name: netraCtRscCustomerInfo
netraCtRscCustomerInfo.description: Customer information used in the message generated for a pager or email alert

netraCtRscVersionBootMajor.name: netraCtRscVersionBootMajor
netraCtRscVersionBootMajor.description: RSC Firmware BootMonitor Revision Major Number

netraCtRscVersionBootMinor.name: netraCtRscVersionBootMinor
netraCtRscVersionBootMinor.description: RSC Firmware BootMonitor Revision Minor Number

netraCtRscVersionBootMicro.name: netraCtRscVersionBootMicro
netraCtRscVersionBootMicro.description: RSC Firmware BootMonitor Revision Micro Number

netraCtRscVersionMainMajor.name: netraCtRscVersionMainMajor
netraCtRscVersionMainMajor.description: RSC Core RSC Revision Major Number

netraCtRscVersionMainMinor.name: netraCtRscVersionMainMinor
netraCtRscVersionMainMinor.description: RSC Core RSC Revision Minor Number

netraCtRscVersionMainMicro.name: netraCtRscVersionMainMicro
netraCtRscVersionMainMicro.description: RSC Core RSC Revision Micro Number

netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMajor.name: netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMajor
netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMajor.description: RSC Core Firmware Revision Major Number

netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMinor.name: netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMinor
netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMinor.description: RSC Core Firmware Revision Minor Number

netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMicro.name: netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMicro
netraCtRscVersionFirmwareMicro.description: RSC Core Firmware Revision Micro Number

netraCtRscEscape.name: netraCtRscEscape
netraCtRscEscape.description: set the first character of the 2-character escape sequence

netraCtRscHostWatchDogReboot.name: netraCtRscHostWatchDogReboot
netraCtRscHostWatchDogReboot.description: RSC monitors a heartbeat from the Solaris host. If this heartbeat is late, then a message will be logged, and an alarm will be set. If netraCtRscHostWatchDogReboot is on, then the solaris host will also be rebooted.

netraCtRscHostWatchDogTimeout.name: netraCtRscHostWatchDogTimeout
netraCtRscHostWatchDogTimeout.description: RSC monitors a heartbeat from the Solaris host. This variable indicates the maximum tolerable number of seconds between heartbeats, before RSC will set alarm0. A setting of 0 indicates that the heartbeat should not be monitored.

netraCtRscPanicDump.name: netraCtRscPanicDump
netraCtRscPanicDump.description: If set to true when netraCtRscAdminHostReset is set, then a break will be sent to the host, causing a core dump to be saved on the host. Otherwise, the setting of netraCtRscAdminHostReset will cause a hardware reset.

netraCtRscCountryCode.name: netraCtRscCountryCode
netraCtRscCountryCode.description: country specified using CCITT internaional dial-plan number.

netraCtRscModemModel.name: netraCtRscModemModel
netraCtRscModemModel.description: the modem type used on the netraCtRsc card.

netraCtRscEnetTpeLinkTest.name: netraCtRscEnetTpeLinkTest
netraCtRscEnetTpeLinkTest.description: Determines whether tpe-link-test should be set of clear. This should be off when interfacing with older-style hubs that don't support heartbeat.

netraCtRscSNMPHostAddress.name: netraCtRscSNMPHostAddress
netraCtRscSNMPHostAddress.description: configured SNMP server for RSC alerts.

netraCtRscMailHostAddressBackup.name: netraCtRscMailHostAddressBackup
netraCtRscMailHostAddressBackup.description: Backup Address of Mail Server. when no IP address is configured for mail server, back up IP address becomes first IP address of mailhost

netraCtRscSystemType.name: netraCtRscSystemType
netraCtRscSystemType.description: System Type. This will currently return one of the following 2 strings: NetraCt400 , or NetraCt800.

netraCtRscPowerSupplyCount.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyCount
netraCtRscPowerSupplyCount.description: The total number of Power Supply FRUs in the platform.

netraCtRscPowerSupplyTable.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyTable
netraCtRscPowerSupplyTable.description: A table listing the characteristics of the Power-Supply FRU.

netraCtRscPowerSupplyEntry.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyEntry
netraCtRscPowerSupplyEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscPowerSupplyTable

netraCtRscPowerSupplyIndex.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyIndex
netraCtRscPowerSupplyIndex.description: Entry number for this Power-Supply FRU row.

netraCtRscPowerSupplyOperState.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyOperState
netraCtRscPowerSupplyOperState.description: The current status of the Power-Supply FRU.

netraCtRscPowerSupplyAdminState.name: netraCtRscPowerSupplyAdminState
netraCtRscPowerSupplyAdminState.description: Setting this value to on(1) requests that the power supply be turned on. Setting this value to off(2) requests that the power supply be turned off.

netraCtRscAlarmCount.name: netraCtRscAlarmCount
netraCtRscAlarmCount.description: Number of Alarm Ports in this Platform

netraCtRscAlarmTable.name: netraCtRscAlarmTable
netraCtRscAlarmTable.description: a table listing the available Alarm Ports.

netraCtRscAlarmEntry.name: netraCtRscAlarmEntry
netraCtRscAlarmEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscAlarmTable.

netraCtRscAlarmIndex.name: netraCtRscAlarmIndex
netraCtRscAlarmIndex.description: row index into Alarm Port table

netraCtRscAlarmID.name: netraCtRscAlarmID
netraCtRscAlarmID.description: Alarm identifier. The current Netra ct 400/800 Alarm Cards currently supports Alarm IDs of 0,1,2, and 3.

netraCtRscAlarmOperState.name: netraCtRscAlarmOperState
netraCtRscAlarmOperState.description: This returns the current value of the Alarm, which may have been set by either software due to environmental conditions, such as Fan failure, or manually, by the setting of netraCtRscAlarmAdminState.

netraCtRscAlarmAdminState.name: netraCtRscAlarmAdminState
netraCtRscAlarmAdminState.description: This reflects the requested state of an alarm port by the SNMP manager.

netraCtRscAlarmPrefix.name: netraCtRscAlarmPrefix
netraCtRscAlarmPrefix.description: The Alarm Prefix that will associate an FRU type to an alarm. Currently supported definitions are: cpuunit(1), software(2), powersupply(3), temperature(4), fan(5). 6 through 9 are reserved for future expansion. 10 through 255 are undefined, and can be configured for user-defined messages and alarming.

netraCtRscFanCount.name: netraCtRscFanCount
netraCtRscFanCount.description: Maximum number of Fan Tray FRUs in Platform

netraCtRscFanTable.name: netraCtRscFanTable
netraCtRscFanTable.description: a table listing the characteristics of the Fan Tray FRU.

netraCtRscFanEntry.name: netraCtRscFanEntry
netraCtRscFanEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscFanTable.

netraCtRscFanIndex.name: netraCtRscFanIndex
netraCtRscFanIndex.description: row index into Fan FRU table

netraCtRscFanStatus.name: netraCtRscFanStatus
netraCtRscFanStatus.description: The current status of the Fan FRU. unknown will be returned if the status is unknown.

netraCtRscTemperatureCount.name: netraCtRscTemperatureCount
netraCtRscTemperatureCount.description: Maximum number of temperature sensors on Platform

netraCtRscTemperatureTable.name: netraCtRscTemperatureTable
netraCtRscTemperatureTable.description: a table listing the contents of the event log as an array of strings.

netraCtRscTemperatureEntry.name: netraCtRscTemperatureEntry
netraCtRscTemperatureEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscTemperatureTable.

netraCtRscTemperatureIndex.name: netraCtRscTemperatureIndex
netraCtRscTemperatureIndex.description: current row of the Temperature sensor

netraCtRscTemperatureValid.name: netraCtRscTemperatureValid
netraCtRscTemperatureValid.description: The current temperature at this sensor is known. If the temperature cannot be obtained, then false will be returned, and netraCtRscTemperatureValue should not be considered to be valid.

netraCtRscTemperatureLowWarn.name: netraCtRscTemperatureLowWarn
netraCtRscTemperatureLowWarn.description: low warning threshold for this temperature sensor

netraCtRscTemperatureHighWarn.name: netraCtRscTemperatureHighWarn
netraCtRscTemperatureHighWarn.description: high warning threshold for this temperature sensor

netraCtRscTemperatureDesc.name: netraCtRscTemperatureDesc
netraCtRscTemperatureDesc.description: textual description of the Temperature sensor

netraCtRscEventLogCount.name: netraCtRscEventLogCount
netraCtRscEventLogCount.description: current number of lines in the event log

netraCtRscEventLogTable.name: netraCtRscEventLogTable
netraCtRscEventLogTable.description: a table listing the contents of the event log as an array of strings.

netraCtRscEventLogEntry.name: netraCtRscEventLogEntry
netraCtRscEventLogEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscEventLogTable.

netraCtRscEventLogIndex.name: netraCtRscEventLogIndex
netraCtRscEventLogIndex.description: The index of the entry. The oldest entry will start at index 0. The most recent entry will be found at the index equal to netraCtRscEventLogCount - 1.

netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogCount.name: netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogCount
netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogCount.description: current number of lines in the original console log.

netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogTable.name: netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogTable
netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogTable.description: a table listing the contents of the original console log as an array of strings.

netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogEntry.name: netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogEntry
netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogTable.

netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogIndex.name: netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogIndex
netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogIndex.description: The index of the entry. The oldest entry will start at index 0. The most recent entry will be found at the index equal to netraCtRscOrigConsoleLogCount - 1.

netraCtRscConsoleLogCount.name: netraCtRscConsoleLogCount
netraCtRscConsoleLogCount.description: current number of lines in the console log.

netraCtRscConsoleLogTable.name: netraCtRscConsoleLogTable
netraCtRscConsoleLogTable.description: a table listing the contents of the console log as an array of strings.

netraCtRscConsoleLogEntry.name: netraCtRscConsoleLogEntry
netraCtRscConsoleLogEntry.description: an entry (conceptual row) in the netraCtRscConsoleLogTable.

netraCtRscConsoleLogIndex.name: netraCtRscConsoleLogIndex
netraCtRscConsoleLogIndex.description: The index of the entry. The oldest entry will start at index 0. The most recent entry will be found at the index equal to netraCtRscConsoleLogCount - 1.

netraCtRscConsoleReset.name: netraCtRscConsoleReset
netraCtRscConsoleReset.description: When set, the console log is reset so that the current log is copied over to the original console log, and the the console log will be cleared. All new console messages will then go to the console log.clear(2) setting is read-only.

netraCtRscRCCPowerOnEnable.name: netraCtRscRCCPowerOnEnable
netraCtRscRCCPowerOnEnable.description: If set to false, masks the RCC PowerOn command.

netraCtRscRCCPowerOffEnable.name: netraCtRscRCCPowerOffEnable
netraCtRscRCCPowerOffEnable.description: If set to false, masks the RCC PowerOff command.

netraCtRscRCCResetEnable.name: netraCtRscRCCResetEnable
netraCtRscRCCResetEnable.description: If set to false, masks the RCC Reset command.

netraCtRscRCCLinkNum.name: netraCtRscRCCLinkNum
netraCtRscRCCLinkNum.description: 2-byte string that defines the RCC Linknum address.

netraCtRscEvent.name: netraCtRscEvent
netraCtRscEvent.description: Event used to notify the snmp manager of a new RSC event. An event is generated when one of the values: netraCtRscAlarmOperState, in the Table:netraCtRscAlarmTable changes state.
